Select the camera in the hierarchy view [A], and look at its camera component in the inspector view. Here we can change the background from blue to another colour [B], and there's also an eyedropper to pick any colour from the screen.\
\
We want something more fancy: a skybox, which is a kind of wraparound image typically used to simulate sky. This camera is already set to render a skybox, but because none is configured, it's falling back to a plain colour.\
\
We can configure a default skybox for all cameras in the project's Render Settings (in the Edit menu), or a custom skybox for individual cameras (which overrides the Render Settings). Let's add a custom skybox for just this camera.\
\
Click the Add Component button [C] and add (under Rendering category) a Skybox component.\
\
