We can see a skybox component [D] now appears in the inspector, but the camera's view is still blue. This is because the skybox component is not yet configured.\
\
We do not have any skybox assets in our project, so we can't configure the component until we create or import one. Unity comes with a few skyboxes, so let's import those.\
\
Right click on Assets in the project view, choose Import Package, Skyboxes [E]. Unity will decompress the package and show an import dialog. This is helpful if we don't want to import all of a package's assets into our project; for now, import all.\
