Unity shows a select material dialog [J] and we can choose among materials in our scene or in our project's assets [K]. We can choose materials (including none) [L] and see both the component's value update, and the game view to reflect the new camera settings, live.\
\
Having configured our skybox, with our camera still selected we can use the rotate tool (E key) to see what it looks like from all angles; we can easily undo our changes (ctrl+Z) to get back to the default camera view (which is looking at the origin from 10 units down the negative z axis, 1 unit high in the y axis).\
